The paper deals with the problem of matching multiple objects in vision and graphics, which is a fundamental problem in computer vision (cs.CV) and computer graphics (cs.GR). The paper also discusses the computational complexity of the problem and proposes an efficient algorithm, which falls under the category of algorithms and data structures (cs.DS) and machine learning (cs.LG). Finally, the paper deals with geometric consistency, which is a topic in computational geometry (cs.CG).
